/** * Rules activity TextViews */ Game rules Goal Winner Score
"To pin opponent's thumb down for certain period of time." "To win a contest 1 player must pin opponent's thumb down for as long as it takes to say: one, two, three, four, I win thumb-o-war!" For every match winner gains 1 point.
"To reach as many points as possible." "The player that has recorded the most points at the end of a game is declared that game's winner." Points can be accumulated by making field goals (two or three points) or free throws (one point). If a player makes a field goal from within the three-point line, the player scores two points. If the player makes a field goal from beyond the three-point line, the player scores three points.
